    select(starts_with("weight_"))


vis_miss(blood_child_weight)

gg_miss_var(blood_child_weight)

1.3 boxplot

# data preparation convert to long format
blood_child_weight_long <- blood_child %>%
    pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("weight_"), names_to = "weight_time", names_prefix = "weight_",
        values_to = "weight_value", values_drop_na = FALSE)


blood_child_weight_long$weight_time <- factor(blood_child_weight_long$weight_time,
    levels = c("del_CN", "del", "wk1", "wk3", "wk6", "m3", "m6", "m12", "m18"))

## assign visit variable
blood_child_weight_long_visit <- blood_child_weight_long %>%
    group_by(Subject_ID) %>%
    arrange(weight_time) %>%
    dplyr::mutate(visit = 1:n()) %>%
    arrange(Subject_ID)
blood_weight_plot1 <- blood_child_weight_long_visit %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = weight_value, fill = weight_time)) + geom_histogram() + facet_grid2(cols = vars(weight_time),
    scale = "free", independent = "all")


blood_weight_plot1

blood_weight_plot2 <- blood_child_weight_long_visit %>%
    ggplot(aes(y = weight_value, x = weight_time, fill = weight_time)) + geom_boxplot()


blood_weight_plot2
